  <front>
   <head>EPIGRAM XV. To CLARISSA.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WHY like a tyrant wilt thou reign,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When thou may'st rule the willing mind?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Can the poor pride of giving pain</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Repay the joys that wait the kind?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I curse my fond enduring heart,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Which scorn'd presumes not to be free,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Condemn'd to feel a double smart,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To hate myself, and burn for thee.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
